oth 'what action is occurring' and 'how it will unfold', enabling accurate classification even under occlusion or ambiguous poses. This eliminates the need for diffusion-based video generation, reducing computational cost by 60% compared to generative approaches while improving temporal coherence. We evaluate on FineGym, SSv2, and UCF101, demonstrating superior performance in zero-shot action anticipation and few-shot recognition. The framework also enables new capabilities such as motion explainability via latent trajectory visualization and proactive decision-making in robotic agents observing static scenes.",
